1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:02,140
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:03,910
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:17,890
I can still see the baby
in your face.

4
00:00:19,790 --> 00:00:23,530
Do I look a lot like her?
My birth mother.

5
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,100
Are you here because
you want to meet her?

6
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:31,640
Yes.

7
00:00:32,340 --> 00:00:35,270
Are you still in touch with her?

8
00:00:35,570 --> 00:00:38,410
Yes, we are. We check in
with each other from time to time.

9
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:41,180
Does she know how I'm doing?

10
00:00:43,380 --> 00:00:44,420
No.

11
00:00:45,050 --> 00:00:47,950
She just knows that
you're doing well.

12
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:53,560
Could I...

13
00:00:54,090 --> 00:00:57,160
possibly get
her contact information?

14
00:01:02,170 --> 00:01:05,000
How about I ask her first?

15
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:07,240
To see if it's okay
to give you her number.

16
00:01:07,770 --> 00:01:08,770
Okay.

17
00:01:10,210 --> 00:01:12,510
Please don't tell her I was here.

18
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:14,080
Just...

19
00:01:14,350 --> 00:01:17,450
Could you just ask
if she's willing to be in touch?

20
00:01:18,050 --> 00:01:19,050
I will.

21
00:01:19,950 --> 00:01:21,150
Thank you.

22
00:01:22,090 --> 00:01:24,660
(3H Acupressure Bed)

23
00:01:39,370 --> 00:01:42,840
Hello, Sister. What's this about?

24
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:47,510
Yes, I can talk for a bit now.

25
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:51,250
This might sound
a bit out of the blue,

26
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:56,620
but what if... What if Veronica...

27
00:01:56,690 --> 00:01:59,460
asked for your number?

28
00:01:59,890 --> 00:02:04,760
She's an adult now, so I figured
something like this might come up.

29
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:08,670
I just thought
I should check with you first.

30
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:13,400
If we get in touch,

31
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:16,710
I'll want to see her.

32
00:02:17,610 --> 00:02:19,980
I suppose you would.

33
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,880
I was afraid I'd want to see her...

34
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,650
That's why I never asked
for updates.

35
00:02:28,790 --> 00:02:31,120
Right.

36
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:35,990
I think it's better if we don't know
anything about each other.

37
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,170
Oh, dear.

38
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,270
Oh, my.

39
00:02:52,410 --> 00:02:54,210
Veronica and I...

40
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:59,020
Each of us has
our own precious family.

41
00:03:18,070 --> 00:03:19,200
So...

42
00:03:20,810 --> 00:03:23,070
she doesn't want to meet me?

43
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:30,050
It's not that
she doesn't want to see you.

44
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:33,280
It's just that you both have
new families that you've found,

45
00:03:33,690 --> 00:03:36,590
and she probably thinks that
cherishing those families...

46
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:39,390
is more important right now.

47
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:44,400
I see.

48
00:03:53,140 --> 00:03:56,270
- Honey.
- Hey, honey. What brings you here?

49
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:02,480
I stopped by the shop and thought
we could head home together.

50
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:05,150
Great. Just give me a second.

51
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:08,750
Did everything go okay today?

52
00:04:08,990 --> 00:04:10,890
Okay? What do you mean?

53
00:04:11,090 --> 00:04:14,130
I was outside for a bit
on a call earlier,

54
00:04:14,290 --> 00:04:17,560
and I saw you talking to someone
with a serious look on your face.

55
00:04:17,730 --> 00:04:22,330
Oh, that was the delivery guy.
He fell and broke a bone.

56
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:25,770
He came for acupuncture by mistake,
so I told him to see an orthopedist.

57
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,540
Just wait a moment. I'm almost done.

58
00:04:29,570 --> 00:04:30,580
Okay.

59
00:04:49,590 --> 00:04:52,360
Thanks for coming with me.

60
00:04:57,140 --> 00:04:59,800
You should've just told her
you were in Korea.

61
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:05,040
She might've asked to see you then.

62
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:10,150
She doesn't even know
I live in the US.

63
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:12,850
All this time,

64
00:05:14,850 --> 00:05:17,760
she's never even seen
a single picture of me.

65
00:05:20,490 --> 00:05:22,260
Even though she abandoned me,

66
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:28,470
I thought she'd miss me
and want to see me.

67
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,700
You know,

68
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:37,040
I feel like I've been abandoned
all over again.

69
00:05:55,590 --> 00:05:58,160
I have stage two breast cancer.

70
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:00,730
I have a favor to ask.

71
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:04,370
Please keep this a secret
from Ju Ah.

72
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:11,380
Why are you barely eating?

73
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:16,450
I'm full just from watching you eat.

74
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:20,490
I don't buy it. What's on your mind?

75
00:06:26,590 --> 00:06:28,030
About us dating...

76
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:30,500
Let's just keep it a secret
a little longer.

77
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:34,670
Why? Are you getting cold feet?

78
00:06:34,970 --> 00:06:36,870
You're already so busy
getting ready,

79
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:39,570
and Dr. Han seems
really stressed out, too.

80
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:43,210
How about after the fashion show?

81
00:06:45,810 --> 00:06:49,110
- All right. I guess that's better.
- Yes.

82
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:54,450
Grandma would never tell Dr. Han
about us.

83
00:06:55,150 --> 00:06:56,850
Of course, she wouldn't.

84
00:06:58,420 --> 00:06:59,660
Hurry up and eat.

85
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:01,090
Okay.

86
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:07,700
Here.

87
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:12,870
How is it?

88
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:16,240
You went easy on the salt purposely,
didn't you?

89
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,680
That's right.
You should eat this way from now on.

90
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,650
It's delicious
no matter how you make it.

91
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:25,450
Now that I'm taking time off,
I'll help with the housework.

92
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:29,790
Time off? This isn't time off.
You're sick, not on a break.

93
00:07:30,290 --> 00:07:33,390
Don't worry about that stuff.
Just focus on getting better.

94
00:07:34,590 --> 00:07:36,790
It's just that I don't know
how to do anything,

95
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:39,900
so you think
I'll just get in the way, right?

96
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,370
Yes.

97
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:45,800
Ju Ah said she'd be late,
but where are Jeong Han and Dae Han?

98
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:47,100
I'm sure they'll be back soon.

99
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:51,480
Right. I think we need
to tell Dae Han.

100
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:55,180
Don't you think
Jeong Han already told him?

101
00:07:57,580 --> 00:07:58,920
Seong Mi...

102
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:02,690
So?

103
00:08:03,490 --> 00:08:05,160
How is she doing now?

104
00:08:05,890 --> 00:08:06,890
What stage did they say it is?

105
00:08:08,090 --> 00:08:09,190
Is it terminal?

106
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:13,100
No. They said it's stage two.

107
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:18,070
The scans don't show
that it's spread,

108
00:08:18,940 --> 00:08:22,740
but we won't know for sure
about the lymph nodes until surgery.

109
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:25,940
That's a relief.

110
00:08:27,380 --> 00:08:28,980
She's so sick, and I was just...

111
00:08:29,710 --> 00:08:31,720
humming away at the dinner table.

112
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:33,890
But you...

113
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:37,890
Didn't you tease her
about menopause?

114
00:08:37,990 --> 00:08:40,060
Yes, I did.

115
00:08:40,890 --> 00:08:42,090
Seriously, what were you thinking?

116
00:08:42,430 --> 00:08:45,260
I had no idea. Darn it.

117
00:08:48,670 --> 00:08:49,970
Who's calling? My gosh.

118
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:53,300
Oh, hey...

119
00:08:54,570 --> 00:08:58,410
It's Seong Mi. It's her.
Hush. Don't cry. Not a sound!

120
00:09:01,780 --> 00:09:04,050
Hey, Seong Mi.

121
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:09,350
Yes, I'm on my way.
I'll be right there. Okay.

122
00:09:11,690 --> 00:09:13,660
Hey, you.

123
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:16,090
You can't cry in front of her.
Got it?

124
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:19,630
Look who's talking.
You'd better not be the one crying.

125
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:24,040
Hey, I'm not going to cry.
I won't cry in front of Seong Mi.

126
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,070
You... You really can't cry.

127
00:09:26,140 --> 00:09:29,140
Okay. Gosh, I'll try. I will.

128
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,910
Hey, you, just...

129
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:35,810
Don't make eye contact with her.
It helped me earlier. Got it?

130
00:09:41,490 --> 00:09:42,490
Hey, I...

131
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:47,120
Hey, I don't think I can do it.

132
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:51,130
Hey, then just keep your eyes open.
Wide, like this.

133
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,730
Like this, see?

134
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:56,930
- How? Like this?
- Yes.

135
00:09:58,740 --> 00:10:00,300
I don't think it's working.

136
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:04,080
Then just jam your hands
in your armpits.

137
00:10:04,140 --> 00:10:06,940
Just try it. Do something.

138
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:09,350
Do what? You want me to do this?

139
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:11,950
Yes, like that!
Just do whatever it takes.

140
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:16,520
It's not going to work!
What am I supposed to do?

141
00:10:16,590 --> 00:10:19,190
What are we going to do?
Gosh, my poor Seong Mi...

142
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:21,760
What's going to happen to her?
I'm losing my mind.

143
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:33,500
For some reason,

144
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:37,270
the side dishes taste
a little bland today.

145
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:43,750
Dae Han,
did you hear about Seong Mi?

146
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,090
I'm fine.

147
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:52,760
I just need the surgery,
so please don't worry. Okay?

148
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:04,170
Hey, what are you doing
in the middle of dinner?

149
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:09,840
Hey, this is actually working.

150
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:14,750
Look, wow.
Hey, look. The tears stopped.

151
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:16,380
No more tears. It really works.

152
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,450
Man, you've got
some serious self-control.

153
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:28,060
Mom, maybe we should switch
to a regular dining table?

154
00:11:28,690 --> 00:11:30,190
It'll be hard on Seong Mi...

155
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:32,260
to keep getting up and down
while she's recovering.

156
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:33,560
Oh, son.

157
00:11:34,270 --> 00:11:36,430
Now, that's what I like to hear.

158
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:38,870
That's so thoughtful of you.

159
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:42,340
Oh, and while we're at it,
let's get a bed for your mom, too.

160
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:45,480
Yes, good idea.
And with Parents' Day coming up...

161
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:48,780
- We'll get you a bed, Mom.
- Oh, yes, let's do that.

162
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:52,050
- It's time to live comfortably.
- Right.

163
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,650
So, what about your job?

164
00:11:56,050 --> 00:11:57,350
What's going to happen with it?

165
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,090
I'm planning to take
a few months off.

166
00:12:00,890 --> 00:12:02,660
I'm actually looking forward to it.
It'll be nice.

167
00:12:03,660 --> 00:12:04,860
You don't have to pretend.

168
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:07,100
You don't have to act
like you're okay.

169
00:12:07,870 --> 00:12:08,870
Listen, Dae Han.

170
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:13,400
It's not a big deal,
so let's not let the kids know.

171
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:16,670
But still, they should know.

172
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,840
This is a critical time for Ju Ah,

173
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:22,150
and I'll wait until Woo Jae is ready
before telling him.

174
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:23,780
Okay.

175
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,020
After the surgery,

176
00:12:26,450 --> 00:12:28,950
your arm's range of motion
will be limited.

177
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:32,660
If you don't do rehab right,
your neck and trapezius...

178
00:12:38,130 --> 00:12:39,400
Your neck and trapezius muscles...

179
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:44,270
It can cause a lot of pain there.
So...

180
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:49,570
I'll look up some research
and help you with your therapy.

181
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,540
Don't you worry about a thing.
I'll take care of everything.

182
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:54,280
Thank you.

183
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:57,110
You're seriously the best.

184
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:00,350
Come on, eat up. Okay?

185
00:13:01,590 --> 00:13:03,190
- You should eat too, Mother.
- Yes.

186
00:13:15,330 --> 00:13:16,330
Hey, Dorphini.

187
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:18,900
Is it busy at the restaurant?

188
00:13:22,770 --> 00:13:25,910
Oh, shoot. Listen,
I can't pick you up tonight.

189
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:28,110
Oh, no, it's not that.

190
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:33,520
Something just came up, that's all.

191
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,090
Okay, sure. What?

192
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:40,090
I'll talk to Woo Jae,
so he can take you home.

193
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:41,960
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

194
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:44,130
Don't worry about it.
I can get home by myself.

195
00:13:45,730 --> 00:13:49,230
Tamin, what's wrong with your voice?
Are you coming down with something?

196
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:52,270
I see. Okay.

197
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:56,210
I'll let you know when I get home.
Bye.

198
00:13:58,640 --> 00:13:59,710
I wonder if he's sick.

199
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:01,450
Is my uncle sick?

200
00:14:03,980 --> 00:14:05,820
How did you know I was on the phone
with your uncle?

201
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:08,790
I didn't.

202
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:11,660
Wait, you were on the phone
with my uncle?

203
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:15,090
No! Why would I be on the phone
with your uncle?

204
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:17,900
I know, right?
No way that would ever happen.

205
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:21,470
- Right? Let's get back to work.
- Okay.

206
00:14:21,530 --> 00:14:24,300
- Excuse me, could we get water?
- Oh, yes. One moment.

207
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,370
Should I have just told her I knew?

208
00:14:29,810 --> 00:14:31,980
Man, this is so hard.

209
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:38,080
Don't pull an all-nighter in vain.
Get some sleep.

210
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:41,090
How did you know I was planning
to pull an all-nighter?

211
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:46,120
Pressure blocks your creativity,
so get some sleep.

212
00:14:46,190 --> 00:14:47,220
Got it.

213
00:14:47,730 --> 00:14:51,160
- Are you heading to your studio?
- No, home. To see Eun Bin.

214
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:54,160
So, does that mean
you're picking me up tomorrow?

215
00:14:54,370 --> 00:14:57,530
No. Drive Dr. Han's car over.

216
00:14:58,070 --> 00:14:59,640
Right, got it.

217
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:02,240
- Bye.
- Bye.

218
00:15:05,810 --> 00:15:06,810
Get home safe.

219
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,250
Go on.

220
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:29,630
VP, what's your schedule like
tomorrow morning?

221
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:31,240
(Hwangbo Hye Su, Vice President,
Strategic Planning Division)

222
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,270
I have a Strategic Planning meeting.
Why?

223
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,610
I have something urgent
to discuss with you tomorrow.

224
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:36,870
What is it?

225
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:40,380
Did you tell Dr. Han you're a couple
and get chewed out for it?

226
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:44,520
That's pretty much
what it felt like.

227
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:46,720
So what is it?

228
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:51,120
Fine. I'll push the morning meeting.
Be in my office first thing.

229
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:52,660
Will do.

230
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:01,100
He wouldn't have said anything
to Ju Ah, right?

231
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:07,440
I'm home.

232
00:16:08,310 --> 00:16:09,370
Ju Ah.

233
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,310
Come in here for a second.

234
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:23,850
What is it, Grandma?

235
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:26,290
What's with that scary look?

236
00:16:28,060 --> 00:16:29,660
Didn't Director Yang
say anything to you?

237
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:35,730
Someone told me
you met with Director Yang.

238
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:40,870
Are you upset with me
for doing that?

239
00:16:42,370 --> 00:16:45,310
No, I understand why you did it.

240
00:16:45,940 --> 00:16:49,310
You've always been on my side,
no matter what I did.

241
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:53,180
So for you to be against this,

242
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:56,020
I know it must be
something really wrong.

243
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:58,960
I'm sorry, Grandma.

244
00:16:59,860 --> 00:17:00,890
But...

245
00:17:02,090 --> 00:17:05,200
I need you to understand
that I can't give up.

246
00:17:06,530 --> 00:17:11,200
Can't you just trust me and wait?
And don't tell anyone. Please?

247
00:17:13,170 --> 00:17:18,280
It's just... I feel like
nothing means anything without him.

248
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:19,880
I told you before.

249
00:17:21,010 --> 00:17:23,110
He's the one who opened up
a whole new world for me.

250
00:17:25,120 --> 00:17:26,220
I know it all.

251
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:28,890
Your pain and how the adults feel...

252
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:33,890
I even know how much our mothers
despise each other.

253
00:17:35,030 --> 00:17:37,090
But even knowing all that,
I still made this choice.

254
00:17:38,230 --> 00:17:41,470
So please, just trust me.
I'm begging you, Grandma.

255
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:46,540
- Ju Ah.
- Grandma.

256
00:17:53,810 --> 00:17:57,180
So when does the shop open?
Are you having a grand opening?

257
00:17:57,510 --> 00:18:01,850
What for? I'm just taking it over,
so I'm planning to start next week.

258
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:02,950
I see.

259
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:06,490
- Dad, when does your shoot wrap up?
- I still have a little more to go.

260
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:09,990
Right. The premiere's this week,
so let's watch it together.

261
00:18:09,990 --> 00:18:11,030
You can make it down, right?

262
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:14,870
It's hectic with the show,
but I'll make time.

263
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:17,330
Hey. Once I get famous,

264
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:19,300
don't you forget about
making me a model.

265
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:22,170
As you can see,
your old man has the looks.

266
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:23,740
I look as good as any model.

267
00:18:24,580 --> 00:18:28,950
- Get famous, then we can talk.
- Hey, it's in the bag.

268
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:32,180
And when you're done shooting,
go spend some time with Se Ri.

269
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,150
Mind your own business.

270
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:38,890
Where's Eun Bin?
I was worried, so I came by.

271
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:41,160
She stepped out.

272
00:18:41,460 --> 00:18:43,490
She did call to say
she'd be late, though.

273
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,200
Gosh, I'm getting sleepy.

274
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:48,070
You should go on to bed.

275
00:18:48,430 --> 00:18:50,530
I'll wait for Eun Bin to come home
and then sleep in Grandpa's room.

276
00:19:00,940 --> 00:19:01,950
Why?

277
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:05,420
It's obvious you've been crying.
They're going to worry.

278
00:19:07,620 --> 00:19:10,120
I'll get some air
and go in a bit later then.

279
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:11,520
Okay.

280
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:13,990
I'll go in first, then.
Take your time.

281
00:19:14,530 --> 00:19:15,530
Okay.

282
00:19:41,990 --> 00:19:42,990
Sweetie!

283
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:45,020
You've been making me
so worried lately.

284
00:19:45,620 --> 00:19:49,030
- You were worried about me?
- Of course! Do you have to ask?

285
00:19:49,690 --> 00:19:51,300
Have you eaten?

286
00:19:51,730 --> 00:19:55,400
I'm good. Min Seo will be back soon,
so please get her something to eat.

287
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,900
Just don't let her come
straight upstairs, okay?

288
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,610
What? What is with her?

289
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:13,120
Min Seo can't see this,
no matter what.

290
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:20,490
Where should I hide this?

291
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:21,860
Hold on.

292
00:20:35,910 --> 00:20:37,980
- What the...
- It's me.

293
00:20:38,180 --> 00:20:41,310
- Why are you here?
- This is our house.

294
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:45,080
This is my room.
Stop barging in here without asking.

295
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:48,090
You're one to talk.
You barged into my apartment.

296
00:20:48,690 --> 00:20:51,620
- I said, why are you here?
- I was worried about you.

297
00:20:52,290 --> 00:20:56,130
Like you've ever worried about me.
You abandoned me to study abroad.

298
00:20:57,030 --> 00:21:00,460
- You'll hold this over me forever?
- Forever. Until the day I die.

299
00:21:02,430 --> 00:21:04,070
So, what were you hiding?

300
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:05,570
Nothing. It was nothing.

301
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:07,340
You're acting suspicious.

302
00:21:07,870 --> 00:21:10,970
Get out, go. Seriously! Out!

303
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:14,380
Here you go.

304
00:21:16,580 --> 00:21:18,450
You really didn't have to.

305
00:21:19,650 --> 00:21:23,620
Where did you two just come from?
Did Eun Bin say anything to you?

306
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:25,920
No.

307
00:21:26,290 --> 00:21:30,290
I was caught up in my own problems,
I didn't get a chance to ask her.

308
00:21:31,530 --> 00:21:34,060
I see. Go on and eat.

309
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:35,300
Okay.

310
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:38,840
I'm sorry
I couldn't help you study today.

311
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:41,740
Right. In that case,
could you take a quick look at this?

312
00:21:41,940 --> 00:21:44,680
- I tried writing an English diary.
- Okay.

313
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:49,510
"Today,
I learn how to run the store."

314
00:21:50,610 --> 00:21:52,580
- How is it? What do you think?
- It's pretty good.

315
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:57,750
But here, you just need to change
the verb "learn" to the past tense.

316
00:21:58,820 --> 00:22:00,890
- Right. Past tense.
- Yes.

317
00:22:00,890 --> 00:22:02,060
Right, I'll just fix it.

318
00:22:02,230 --> 00:22:04,490
- What are you two doing?
- Oh, no.

319
00:22:04,860 --> 00:22:07,200
What on earth are you hiding?
Give it to me.

320
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:09,030
- Wait, Eun Bin, that's not it...
- Give it to me!

321
00:22:10,970 --> 00:22:12,000
What is this?

322
00:22:13,340 --> 00:22:16,510
I've been teaching your mom
some English.

323
00:22:16,570 --> 00:22:19,140
So you're learning English
from Min Seo?

324
00:22:19,910 --> 00:22:21,180
And here I thought
it was something serious.

325
00:22:21,580 --> 00:22:23,510
Why were you so secretive about it?

326
00:22:23,580 --> 00:22:25,680
I was just a little embarrassed,
that's all.

327
00:22:26,750 --> 00:22:29,850
I'll leave you to talk.
I'm going to go rest.

328
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:34,690
- Thank you for the snack.
- No problem.

329
00:22:37,660 --> 00:22:42,000
Starting a business and studying.
You're amazing.

330
00:22:42,530 --> 00:22:46,840
Your father will be a councilman.
I can't be an embarrassment to him.

331
00:22:47,070 --> 00:22:50,570
Good for you. Pursue what you want.
Just go for it.

332
00:22:51,610 --> 00:22:54,210
I'm going to get
some certifications, too.

333
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:58,220
This business will be a success.
And I'm going to make a fortune.

334
00:22:58,320 --> 00:22:59,720
That way,

335
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:01,790
I can provide the capital
for Eun Bin's business.

336
00:23:03,720 --> 00:23:06,290
Do you really think I don't know
why you've been acting this way?

337
00:23:07,060 --> 00:23:08,060
And why is that?

338
00:23:08,130 --> 00:23:09,630
You're used to being lazy,

339
00:23:09,630 --> 00:23:11,290
so you're struggling
with having to work.

340
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:13,600
- Right?
- Is that what this is about?

341
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:17,700
You pushed too hard to impress
Grandpa and Dad and burned out.

342
00:23:18,540 --> 00:23:22,170
I'm going to help you now,
so just take it easy. Okay?

343
00:23:22,610 --> 00:23:24,240
That's not it at all.

344
00:23:24,510 --> 00:23:27,280
Must be nice, Eun Bin.
You have someone solid on your side.

345
00:23:29,310 --> 00:23:32,020
Why are you always so good to me?

346
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:35,020
What do you mean? I'm your mom.

347
00:23:36,620 --> 00:23:40,420
But I'm not your real daughter.
Aren't I a nuisance to you?

348
00:23:40,490 --> 00:23:43,060
Oh, boy.
When are you going to grow up?

349
00:23:44,490 --> 00:23:46,630
Yang Eun Bin. Yang Hyun Bin.

350
00:23:47,260 --> 00:23:49,500
You're both my children.

351
00:23:50,170 --> 00:23:53,640
Of course,
since I'm so young and beautiful,

352
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,870
it's pretty obvious I'm the stepmom.

353
00:23:57,110 --> 00:24:01,010
But in my heart, I've always been
a real mother to you.

354
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:03,280
I think so, too.

355
00:24:03,950 --> 00:24:06,350
I honestly don't want anything more.

356
00:24:06,820 --> 00:24:10,950
I just want our family
to stay this happy forever.

357
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,170
What on earth is going on with her?

358
00:24:29,540 --> 00:24:31,710
She's not answering my texts
or my calls.

359
00:24:32,580 --> 00:24:34,210
(My dearest Woo Jae, good morning!)

360
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:37,310
My dearest Woo Jae, good morning!

361
00:24:37,380 --> 00:24:40,380
I'm so excited just thinking
about seeing my Woo Jae today...

362
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:45,290
that I tossed and turned all night.
Let's have a great shift, okay?

363
00:24:45,390 --> 00:24:46,660
See you later.

364
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:52,830
(Want to go to work together
to see you sooner?)

365
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:54,430
(No response from you,
but I'll miss you anyway!)

366
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:55,570
(Woo Jae, I really miss you.
Don't you miss me?)

367
00:24:57,230 --> 00:24:59,540
Have I really not texted her back
this whole time?

368
00:25:05,110 --> 00:25:06,910
What are you writing so intensely?

369
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:09,480
Oh, it's a mood journal.

370
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:13,720
Isn't that what you have
your patients write?

371
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:15,620
I'm a patient too, you know.

372
00:25:18,220 --> 00:25:22,160
Once treatment starts and I'm weak,
my mood swings will get worse.

373
00:25:22,390 --> 00:25:24,490
So I need to manage
my own mental state.

374
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:27,360
Yes, right.

375
00:25:28,570 --> 00:25:31,430
For someone
who's always built their life...

376
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:34,300
around their career
and achievements like I have,

377
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:36,040
the anxiety comes more...

378
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:39,440
from losing control
than from the illness.

379
00:25:43,010 --> 00:25:45,680
What is it?
Can't you sleep with the light on?

380
00:25:46,450 --> 00:25:48,690
No, it's not that.
I'm going to sleep.

381
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:08,370
Hey, Gong Woo Jae,
can you not stomp around like that?

382
00:26:10,070 --> 00:26:11,070
What, me?

383
00:26:11,140 --> 00:26:14,280
Yes, you. I couldn't sleep a wink
thanks to you stomping around.

384
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:17,710
Excuse me,
but you look like you slept well.

385
00:26:18,180 --> 00:26:19,850
If you get home late,
just go to bed.

386
00:26:19,850 --> 00:26:21,180
Why did you have to shower?

387
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:25,290
The shower, the hair dryer...
I thought I was going to lose it.

388
00:26:25,390 --> 00:26:27,690
So what? I got home after working
all day at a BBQ joint,

389
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:30,790
reeking of meat,
and I'm not supposed to shower?

390
00:26:31,230 --> 00:26:34,900
Still, that's so inconsiderate
to your roommate.

391
00:26:35,470 --> 00:26:36,770
You've got to be kidding me...

392
00:26:37,130 --> 00:26:39,900
You were way louder
when I was trying to study.

393
00:26:40,740 --> 00:26:44,570
When your sister points out flaws,
you fix them. End of story.

394
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:47,280
Did you and Hyun Bin break up?

395
00:26:47,540 --> 00:26:48,550
Of course not.

396
00:26:48,610 --> 00:26:51,280
Then what? Did Grandma tell you
to break up with Hyun Bin?

397
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:52,750
Are you taking it out on me?

398
00:26:52,850 --> 00:26:57,120
Hey, I'm not "taking it out."
It's righteous indignation. You...

399
00:26:57,290 --> 00:26:59,690
Do you have any idea
how important this fashion show is?

400
00:27:02,390 --> 00:27:04,560
- What are you doing?
- Look, Ju Ah.

401
00:27:05,460 --> 00:27:09,400
Whether it's Jun Hyeok or Hyun Bin,
I won't say a word.

402
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:13,440
Just get married and move out.
I can't live with you anymore.

403
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:14,440
Gosh, seriously...

404
00:27:14,970 --> 00:27:17,310
The nerve of that kid.

405
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:19,840
Gosh, I'm so furious.

406
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:24,610
A dining table? Awesome!
It'll be so great to have one.

407
00:27:24,910 --> 00:27:27,120
I know, right?
Best news I've heard all day.

408
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:29,120
He said he's getting
Grandma a bed, too.

409
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:31,720
Really? What's gotten into him?

410
00:27:32,190 --> 00:27:34,290
Parents' Day is coming up, you know.

411
00:27:35,090 --> 00:27:36,290
You guys
should prepare something, too.

412
00:27:37,060 --> 00:27:38,230
I'm one of your parents, you know.

413
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:44,370
Is it just me,
or is the food a little bland today?

414
00:27:47,740 --> 00:27:49,970
What? Is it just me?

415
00:27:51,070 --> 00:27:52,880
Maybe help out
before you complain about the food.

416
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:54,540
Hey, I do my share!

417
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:59,150
Actually, I asked Grandma
to make it less salty.

418
00:27:59,750 --> 00:28:02,990
I have to walk in the fashion show,
and you told me to lose weight.

419
00:28:03,750 --> 00:28:06,660
Dr. Han,
it's time you came to your senses.

420
00:28:06,860 --> 00:28:07,860
Good call.

421
00:28:10,090 --> 00:28:14,460
Why is everyone ganging up on me?
What did I do that was so wrong?

422
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:15,900
Nothing.

423
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:19,140
Come on, everyone, let's eat.
We're going to be late. Okay?

424
00:28:29,780 --> 00:28:30,810
Hey, you little brat!

425
00:28:31,380 --> 00:28:35,550
I get that you work for your aunt,
but why do you keep skipping work?

426
00:28:35,690 --> 00:28:38,420
Keep it up, and I'm telling your mom
and having you fired, you hear me?

427
00:28:38,860 --> 00:28:41,420
Go ahead.
I was going to quit anyway.

428
00:28:41,790 --> 00:28:43,260
What? You're serious?

429
00:28:43,430 --> 00:28:47,530
I feel bad about lying to my mom,

430
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:49,470
and I'm going to look
for an actual job at a bookstore.

431
00:28:49,770 --> 00:28:50,770
I'm sorry, Auntie.

432
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:53,640
Weren't you only working
because of Woo Jae?

433
00:28:54,470 --> 00:28:56,510
- I was.
- So?

434
00:28:57,510 --> 00:28:58,980
Are you giving up on Woo Jae?

435
00:28:59,580 --> 00:29:02,610
What's there to give up on?
He was never mine to begin with.

436
00:29:03,010 --> 00:29:05,120
Goodness, what's gotten into you?

437
00:29:05,180 --> 00:29:07,350
You were fine with it before. Why?

438
00:29:07,550 --> 00:29:09,050
Is it because Woo Jae likes Min Seo?

439
00:29:09,390 --> 00:29:11,590
Gosh, can you just...
Get out, will you?

440
00:29:11,790 --> 00:29:14,760
Hey, I got the impression
Woo Jae was waiting for you.

441
00:29:16,130 --> 00:29:18,860
He was probably waiting for me
because we're short-staffed.

442
00:29:19,460 --> 00:29:20,460
You think so?

443
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:24,870
Where do I find another part-timer?
I can't ask Min Seo to come back.

444
00:29:25,270 --> 00:29:28,140
Why would you?
She's going back to the US anyway.

445
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:30,840
- Just hire someone new.
- Did you two get into a fight?

446
00:29:31,410 --> 00:29:33,480
You two were acting like sisters
just the other day.

447
00:29:34,210 --> 00:29:35,480
Come on down, it's time to eat.

448
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,280
Sisters?

449
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:41,480
I guess we are sisters.

450
00:29:46,290 --> 00:29:47,560
Se Ri, take this.

451
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:50,790
My gosh. What is this, Father?

452
00:29:51,090 --> 00:29:53,500
You'll have a lot of expenses
when you start your business.

453
00:29:53,900 --> 00:29:54,900
Use this for your expenses.

454
00:29:55,630 --> 00:29:58,870
Father, just getting me the shop
was more than I deserved.

455
00:29:59,270 --> 00:30:00,840
My arm is getting sore.

456
00:30:02,810 --> 00:30:05,310
In that case... Thank you, Father.

457
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:09,050
What about me? Dad, me too!

458
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:12,420
What?
Are you just going to skip me, Dad?

459
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:15,750
Mom, if you beg like that,
you'll end up with nothing.

460
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:20,290
- Dad, you got anything?
- Of course, I do.

461
00:30:20,590 --> 00:30:23,260
Abracadabra, alakazam.

462
00:30:25,300 --> 00:30:26,300
Here you go, honey.

463
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:29,170
From now on, stop renting
and just buy designer things.

464
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:31,030
Honey.

465
00:30:31,530 --> 00:30:34,840
That's right. Going to work daily,
you need to mind your wardrobe.

466
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:36,640
My gosh.

467
00:30:38,580 --> 00:30:39,640
Well, then...

468
00:30:41,210 --> 00:30:42,250
Thank you, honey.

469
00:30:42,610 --> 00:30:46,380
Thank you, Father.
I'm so lucky to be in this family.

470
00:30:46,750 --> 00:30:47,950
I'm just so happy today.

471
00:30:48,750 --> 00:30:50,190
Congratulations, ma'am.

472
00:30:50,950 --> 00:30:51,960
Thank you.

473
00:30:53,490 --> 00:30:55,020
Wow, you all really surprised me.

474
00:30:57,990 --> 00:30:59,730
(Han Seong Mi
Neuropsychiatric Clinic)

475
00:31:00,900 --> 00:31:03,700
- Good morning.
- You're in today?

476
00:31:04,130 --> 00:31:07,600
Hey, what's with that reaction?
We made a deal, remember?

477
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:11,640
- Not to treat me like a patient.
- I know, but still...

478
00:31:11,740 --> 00:31:13,680
I'm telling you, I'm really fine.

479
00:31:14,110 --> 00:31:17,710
I'll be back after a short break,
so let's not make it a thing, okay?

480
00:31:18,380 --> 00:31:19,850
- Okay.
- Okay.

481
00:31:21,450 --> 00:31:23,820
(Han Seong Mi)

482
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:37,070
(Taehan Group)

483
00:31:37,130 --> 00:31:39,040
Are you sure she'll be fine
with just the surgery?

484
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:40,800
She has to be.

485
00:31:41,940 --> 00:31:42,940
My goodness.

486
00:31:43,710 --> 00:31:44,810
I can't believe this is happening.

487
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:48,980
She said she'll stop her activities
after the fashion show...

488
00:31:49,550 --> 00:31:52,320
and asked us to either terminate
or amend her contract.

489
00:31:53,220 --> 00:31:54,820
I told her there's no need for that.

490
00:31:55,650 --> 00:31:56,650
You did the right thing.

491
00:31:58,690 --> 00:32:00,160
Speaking of which, poor Ms. Gong.

492
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,230
She'll take it hard
when she finds out.

493
00:32:05,660 --> 00:32:07,730
If Dr. Han needs anything,
request it immediately.

494
00:32:09,430 --> 00:32:10,430
Thanks.

495
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:15,710
What? Why not? I thought you'd tell
Dr. Han you're dating Director Yang.

496
00:32:16,170 --> 00:32:20,410
No, I feel like I should tell her
we broke up first.

497
00:32:21,540 --> 00:32:24,850
But if you tell her about it now,
it solves everything in one go.

498
00:32:25,180 --> 00:32:28,080
Gosh, but that would be too much
of a shock for her.

499
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:31,290
What if she gets so shocked
she messes up her fashion show?

500
00:32:33,290 --> 00:32:36,830
So when are you planning
to tell her?

501
00:32:37,290 --> 00:32:38,490
After the fashion show.

502
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:42,500
So when are you going to tell her
we broke up?

503
00:32:43,130 --> 00:32:44,970
At the next runway practice?

504
00:32:46,940 --> 00:32:48,910
If I could actually
travel back in time,

505
00:32:49,270 --> 00:32:53,010
I would stop myself from ever
visiting your family. Seriously.

506
00:32:53,210 --> 00:32:55,310
Come on. We had no choice.

507
00:32:56,510 --> 00:33:01,180
Hey, if you tell her we broke up,
Dr. Han wouldn't grab me and...

508
00:33:01,220 --> 00:33:03,190
try to force us
to get back together, right?

509
00:33:04,650 --> 00:33:05,660
She probably would.

510
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:21,800
My gosh!

511
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:27,380
- Why are you running? Be careful.
- I was just happy to see you.

512
00:33:27,940 --> 00:33:32,350
- The VP wanted to see you? Why?
- What? It was just about work.

513
00:33:33,020 --> 00:33:36,420
She asked if you'd told my mom
that we're dating, right?

514
00:33:36,950 --> 00:33:38,920
What? No.

515
00:33:39,260 --> 00:33:40,760
Then what did you talk about?

516
00:33:41,290 --> 00:33:45,630
Come on. Why do you need to know
every detail of our discussion?

517
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:50,430
What's this?
Why are you being so evasive?

518
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:52,570
Me? No way.

519
00:33:53,170 --> 00:33:56,070
By the way, babe.
What did you pick for Parents' Day?

520
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:59,480
Right.
I was just trying to figure it out.

521
00:33:59,710 --> 00:34:01,210
My dad already set the bar
pretty high.

522
00:34:01,310 --> 00:34:04,850
How about a water ionizer?
I got one for my parents before,

523
00:34:04,910 --> 00:34:05,920
and they absolutely loved it.

524
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:09,290
That's a great idea. Thanks.

525
00:34:09,850 --> 00:34:11,350
I know my mom will be mad...

526
00:34:11,350 --> 00:34:13,860
when I tell her
I broke up with Jun Hyeok,

527
00:34:14,020 --> 00:34:15,430
so I need a good peace offering.

528
00:34:16,260 --> 00:34:17,490
Let's hurry.
We'll be late for the meeting.

529
00:34:17,860 --> 00:34:18,860
Okay, let's go.

530
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:22,770
This fashion show...

531
00:34:23,030 --> 00:34:26,040
is an important event
that showcases our brand's vision.

532
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:30,510
The show's success will determine
if we get orders from global buyers.

533
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:32,110
Global buyers?

534
00:34:32,280 --> 00:34:34,840
Yes. From Europe and China.

535
00:34:34,910 --> 00:34:37,180
We've invited some major buyers
with serious purchasing power.

536
00:34:37,680 --> 00:34:38,880
As expected.

537
00:34:39,450 --> 00:34:42,080
Our Director Yang
always exceeds expectations.

538
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:45,790
Then our brand's global expansion...

539
00:34:46,720 --> 00:34:48,060
rests on Ms. Gong's shoulders?

540
00:34:49,660 --> 00:34:53,300
I need everyone to support Ms. Gong
and do their absolute best.

541
00:34:54,100 --> 00:34:55,100
- Yes.
- Yes.

542
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:59,940
And since Dr. Han Seong Mi
is not a professional model,

543
00:35:00,300 --> 00:35:03,340
we should choose an outfit
that doesn't restrict her movement.

544
00:35:03,810 --> 00:35:06,610
Yes, I'm already altering it
to be less form-fitting.

545
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:11,610
Is there a private dressing room
for Dr. Han at the venue?

546
00:35:12,050 --> 00:35:14,520
No. Should I set one up, Director?

547
00:35:14,780 --> 00:35:18,290
Yes. And please keep her rehearsals
to an absolute minimum.

548
00:35:18,450 --> 00:35:20,690
Understood.
I'll double-check and report back.

549
00:35:20,790 --> 00:35:25,730
Okay. Remember, our top priority
is Dr. Han's well-being.

550
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:28,870
Let's make sure
she doesn't push herself too hard.

551
00:35:28,870 --> 00:35:29,870
- Right.
- Yes.

552
00:35:29,870 --> 00:35:30,930
- Got it.
- Got it.

553
00:35:31,500 --> 00:35:33,240
(Damga Charcoal Grill,
Onjeong Market)

554
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:36,240
Eun Bin is quitting her job?
Why, all of a sudden?

555
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:41,210
Her mom offered her startup money,
so I guess she just up and quit.

556
00:35:42,080 --> 00:35:43,780
I see.

557
00:35:46,020 --> 00:35:47,150
Hey...

558
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:50,520
Is something going on at home,
by any chance?

559
00:35:51,290 --> 00:35:52,490
No, why do you ask?

560
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:54,620
No reason. Just wondering.

561
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:03,700
Hey, it looks like
we need a new part-timer.

562
00:36:04,070 --> 00:36:07,540
Can you post a job ad online for me?
I have to run a quick errand.

563
00:36:07,770 --> 00:36:08,770
Sure.

564
00:36:14,140 --> 00:36:15,180
Welcome.

565
00:36:17,710 --> 00:36:20,020
My gosh. What brings you here?

566
00:36:21,650 --> 00:36:23,490
You dropped by unannounced, too.

567
00:36:25,860 --> 00:36:27,490
I couldn't come empty-handed,

568
00:36:27,790 --> 00:36:30,360
so I brought you some freesias.
I know they're your favorite.

569
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:35,060
Please take them.
It's not the flowers' fault, is it?

570
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:43,570
I hear you talked to Ju Ah's mom.

571
00:36:44,870 --> 00:36:45,880
Yes.

572
00:36:46,410 --> 00:36:49,550
Thank you for keeping this a secret
from Ju Ah.

573
00:36:50,580 --> 00:36:51,580
I...

574
00:36:52,010 --> 00:36:55,250
truly believe Dr. Han
will recover and make a comeback.

575
00:36:57,290 --> 00:36:58,750
Yes. She has to.

576
00:36:59,620 --> 00:37:01,660
And I'm sorry to say this,

577
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:05,160
but I'm afraid
I have to go against your wishes.

578
00:37:09,700 --> 00:37:12,300
You see, I made a promise to Ju Ah.

579
00:37:13,170 --> 00:37:16,570
I promised I'd protect her
and never let her get hurt or upset.

580
00:37:19,810 --> 00:37:20,840
I'm sorry, but...

581
00:37:21,980 --> 00:37:24,650
I still don't approve of you two.

582
00:37:25,150 --> 00:37:29,090
But you'd be more disappointed in me
if I left Ju Ah, wouldn't you?

583
00:37:30,690 --> 00:37:34,890
I'll take full care of Dr. Han
until the show's over,

584
00:37:35,220 --> 00:37:39,030
and I'll do my best to support Ju Ah
so she can finish her fashion show.

585
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:41,560
So I came to tell you not to worry.

586
00:37:43,270 --> 00:37:44,270
Look.

587
00:37:44,830 --> 00:37:46,840
For the two people you love,

588
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:49,140
I will do my absolute best.

589
00:37:53,940 --> 00:37:56,650
(Pharmacy)

590
00:38:00,180 --> 00:38:01,920
What are you doing here
all of a sudden?

591
00:38:02,550 --> 00:38:04,050
What if your brother catches you?

592
00:38:05,020 --> 00:38:06,190
I missed you.

593
00:38:07,020 --> 00:38:08,790
And you sounded down yesterday.

594
00:38:10,290 --> 00:38:14,130
Besides, my dad and brother are out,
so we're safe.

595
00:38:16,270 --> 00:38:17,370
Is something wrong?

596
00:38:18,070 --> 00:38:19,070
What?

597
00:38:22,200 --> 00:38:24,140
No. And even if there was,
it's fine.

598
00:38:24,640 --> 00:38:25,840
When I look at you,
my little lettuce,

599
00:38:26,380 --> 00:38:28,580
I just forget all my troubles.

600
00:38:33,350 --> 00:38:35,620
Why? Are you having a hard time?

601
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:37,720
No, it's just...

602
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:40,190
It's just an expression.

603
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:45,290
As long as nothing's wrong,
I should get going.

604
00:38:45,290 --> 00:38:48,960
Okay. I'll be sure to pick you up
after work today, okay?

605
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,770
- Okay.
- Now, hurry. Go.

606
00:38:51,670 --> 00:38:53,440
Okay, I'm going.
My gosh, you startled me!

607
00:38:54,070 --> 00:38:56,870
- My goodness.
- Must be nice.

608
00:38:57,410 --> 00:39:01,240
- No, it's not what it looks like...
- It's okay, Dorphini.

609
00:39:01,710 --> 00:39:03,810
Nurse Oh already knows.

610
00:39:05,450 --> 00:39:06,450
I see.

611
00:39:06,950 --> 00:39:07,950
So what brings you here?

612
00:39:08,380 --> 00:39:09,450
What do you think?

613
00:39:09,790 --> 00:39:14,390
You two were getting all cuddly
in broad daylight. I'm here...

614
00:39:14,860 --> 00:39:16,390
to run interference
so you don't get caught.

615
00:39:17,490 --> 00:39:18,490
Thank you.

616
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:22,300
- I'll be off, then.
- Okay, go on. Be careful.

617
00:39:22,770 --> 00:39:23,770
Yes, see you later.

618
00:39:25,940 --> 00:39:28,340
I'm so envious, it's not even funny.

619
00:39:29,270 --> 00:39:30,270
Life's short.

620
00:39:31,340 --> 00:39:32,540
Don't think too far ahead.

621
00:39:34,610 --> 00:39:36,210
Don't be afraid. Just go for it.

622
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:38,050
Be brave and take what you want.

623
00:39:38,550 --> 00:39:39,550
Got it?

624
00:39:40,580 --> 00:39:41,580
Whatever.

625
00:39:45,150 --> 00:39:46,290
My gosh! You scared me!

626
00:39:47,290 --> 00:39:49,390
What are you so jumpy for?
You act like you've never seen me.

627
00:39:49,660 --> 00:39:50,660
Well...

628
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:54,300
It's a shock to see you in daylight.
What's it to you?

629
00:39:55,830 --> 00:39:57,000
Anyway,
shouldn't you be at the restaurant?

630
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:58,330
What are you doing here?

631
00:39:59,400 --> 00:40:02,070
What do you mean?
I was just passing by.

632
00:40:09,610 --> 00:40:10,880
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Pharmacy)

633
00:40:12,050 --> 00:40:13,280
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Hope Supermarket)

634
00:40:16,120 --> 00:40:17,120
My gosh.

635
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:18,790
And what are you doing here?

636
00:40:21,220 --> 00:40:24,960
- Why are you here?
- To get some medicine. Yes.

637
00:40:29,670 --> 00:40:33,170
Hey, Director Song.
You heard about Seong Mi, right?

638
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:37,040
Yes, man. I can't believe it.
She was at the top of her game.

639
00:40:38,210 --> 00:40:39,310
Tell me about it.

640
00:40:40,380 --> 00:40:43,150
Still, they caught it early,
so she should be okay.

641
00:40:43,410 --> 00:40:44,910
Yes, of course. She has to be.

642
00:40:45,550 --> 00:40:48,780
Hey, so what's going to happen
with Seong Mi's job?

643
00:40:49,420 --> 00:40:51,220
Seong Mi says she's fine,

644
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:53,090
but I was wondering
what's next for her.

645
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:57,230
This business isn't a place
for emotional decisions, you know.

646
00:40:57,290 --> 00:41:00,360
We'll have to see how she recovers
before deciding if she can return.

647
00:41:01,230 --> 00:41:02,900
I see.

648
00:41:03,330 --> 00:41:04,530
Still, I'm worried.

649
00:41:04,900 --> 00:41:07,140
If she takes a break from practice
and the show...

650
00:41:08,770 --> 00:41:10,710
Hey, why don't you
do a show instead?

651
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:15,110
Something like a medical show
or a health advice segment.

652
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:18,080
Come on. You think I could do that?

653
00:41:18,450 --> 00:41:20,680
Didn't you say you're going to be
on "Human Theater?"

654
00:41:21,120 --> 00:41:22,520
Hey, you want me to try
and set something up?

655
00:41:22,890 --> 00:41:26,590
Yes. I'll try anything. Seriously.
Could you look into it for me?

656
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:29,490
Yes, okay. Thanks.

657
00:41:32,060 --> 00:41:33,230
What the heck? Seriously.

658
00:41:33,930 --> 00:41:36,530
Hey, were you just eavesdropping
on my call?

659
00:41:37,100 --> 00:41:39,270
No, I just got here.

660
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:40,700
No? Then what is it?

661
00:41:41,240 --> 00:41:43,410
What's so important
you had to come all this way?

662
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:46,180
You want me to make you look good
at tomorrow's shoot...

663
00:41:46,180 --> 00:41:47,780
with Councilor Hwang?

664
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:49,750
- That's not it.
- Then what?

665
00:41:55,580 --> 00:41:56,720
This weekend...

666
00:41:57,920 --> 00:41:59,460
Are you going back to Seongdam?

667
00:42:00,820 --> 00:42:02,460
I don't know.

668
00:42:03,190 --> 00:42:05,830
I'll just come up empty again
if I go without any leads,

669
00:42:06,130 --> 00:42:07,530
so I'm still figuring out
what to do.

670
00:42:08,760 --> 00:42:11,500
My wife said we should file
a missing person report.

671
00:42:12,700 --> 00:42:15,000
And I'm starting to think
that's a good idea.

672
00:42:15,770 --> 00:42:19,410
No. I think we should ask our mother
about that first.

673
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:30,150
I'm heading to the police station.
Want to come?

674
00:42:30,820 --> 00:42:32,220
Our lunch break is almost over.

675
00:42:32,820 --> 00:42:33,860
No, wait.

676
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:36,490
Why would I go there?

677
00:42:36,990 --> 00:42:38,160
Well, earlier...

678
00:42:38,830 --> 00:42:42,530
I was just asking in case
my advice gave you some courage.

679
00:42:42,930 --> 00:42:44,600
You think courage just appears
in five minutes?

680
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:47,400
You go ahead. I'm good.

681
00:42:48,140 --> 00:42:50,070
All right, then.

682
00:42:55,950 --> 00:42:57,450
- Thank you.
- Of course.

683
00:42:57,910 --> 00:43:00,180
If there's no contact
for a long time...

684
00:43:00,180 --> 00:43:01,950
and their status is unknown,

685
00:43:02,150 --> 00:43:03,590
that meets the criteria
for filing a report.

686
00:43:04,090 --> 00:43:08,020
But without official records,
it's very hard to track them.

687
00:43:08,420 --> 00:43:09,860
I see.

688
00:43:10,690 --> 00:43:13,500
- So you're saying it won't be easy?
- That's right.

689
00:43:13,600 --> 00:43:15,400
You should've looked into it sooner.

690
00:43:15,560 --> 00:43:18,530
Right, well...
There were circumstances.

691
00:43:18,870 --> 00:43:22,570
- Still, why not file a report?
- What?

692
00:43:22,970 --> 00:43:25,340
I'll have to discuss that
with my family first.

693
00:43:25,540 --> 00:43:28,980
So you're just asking around
on your own right now?

694
00:43:29,510 --> 00:43:33,280
That's right. I have photos,
but they're all old.

695
00:43:33,350 --> 00:43:36,190
- I see.
- Oh, if you have old photos,

696
00:43:36,320 --> 00:43:38,290
an AI can age them to look current.

697
00:43:38,820 --> 00:43:41,760
That's right.
The things they can do these days.

698
00:43:42,090 --> 00:43:45,530
It won't be an exact match,
but it will be a lot more helpful.

699
00:43:45,730 --> 00:43:47,660
Yes. Thank you.

700
00:43:48,700 --> 00:43:50,900
- Use an AI.
- I'll be off, then.

701
00:43:50,970 --> 00:43:52,800
- Okay, then.
- Thank you.

702
00:43:52,870 --> 00:43:54,340
- All right, take care.
- Take care.

703
00:43:54,740 --> 00:43:55,800
Bye.

704
00:43:57,340 --> 00:43:59,270
(Information)

705
00:44:00,080 --> 00:44:01,710
Why did you turn her down so coldly?

706
00:44:02,210 --> 00:44:03,680
You should've taken your shot
when you had the chance.

707
00:44:04,180 --> 00:44:07,620
Oh, thank you for your concern.

708
00:44:07,950 --> 00:44:09,180
And I'm sorry.

709
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:11,120
Look.

710
00:44:11,920 --> 00:44:12,920
Have some courage.

711
00:44:13,590 --> 00:44:14,720
Go after what you want.

712
00:44:14,820 --> 00:44:19,560
No, it's not that.
I just think it's best for Jin Ah.

713
00:44:19,730 --> 00:44:22,660
You young people make everything
so complicated.

714
00:44:24,300 --> 00:44:25,300
Don't forget that.

715
00:44:59,870 --> 00:45:01,340
- Hey, Dae Han.
- What?

716
00:45:01,500 --> 00:45:05,270
Let's see if any of these will work,
okay?

717
00:45:05,410 --> 00:45:09,650
- Hey, you got any photos?
- Yes, I do. Do you want to see?

718
00:45:10,310 --> 00:45:11,310
What's this?

719
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:13,720
Here.

720
00:45:14,220 --> 00:45:15,220
What?

721
00:45:16,490 --> 00:45:18,720
It's a photo from when
I was on leave from the army.

722
00:45:19,190 --> 00:45:21,060
It's the last picture
I ever took with our father.

723
00:45:21,390 --> 00:45:24,590
Days after I returned to base,
I heard he'd gone missing.

724
00:45:25,990 --> 00:45:27,660
Yes. That's right.

725
00:45:29,100 --> 00:45:30,200
Guess what's in here.

726
00:45:30,870 --> 00:45:32,070
What's that now?

727
00:45:36,710 --> 00:45:39,680
- What?
- It's money Dad gave me on leave.

728
00:45:40,140 --> 00:45:42,140
You're kidding.
You've kept this all this time?

729
00:45:42,540 --> 00:45:43,780
Yes. How could I spend it?

730
00:45:44,180 --> 00:45:46,450
Come on,
you should've just spent it.

731
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:49,020
I just couldn't bring myself to.

732
00:45:50,050 --> 00:45:53,490
I felt like if I spent it,
I'd never see Dad again.

733
00:45:58,490 --> 00:46:01,360
- Upload Dad's photo to an AI,
- Yes.

734
00:46:01,600 --> 00:46:05,300
and ask it what he'd look like now.
It'll do it in a flash.

735
00:46:06,570 --> 00:46:08,540
Wow, technology is amazing
these days.

736
00:46:09,470 --> 00:46:11,970
Just give it a second.
It'll be done in a flash.

737
00:46:17,250 --> 00:46:19,010
- Here it comes.
- Yes, wow.

738
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:22,150
- Wow, this is incredible, right?
- Yes.

739
00:46:24,190 --> 00:46:25,190
My gosh.

740
00:46:32,390 --> 00:46:35,030
(Project, generate image)

741
00:46:40,540 --> 00:46:43,910
(Project, generate image)

742
00:46:43,910 --> 00:46:44,970
(Missing Person, Gong Gi Cheol)

743
00:46:44,970 --> 00:46:46,010
What do you think, Mom?

744
00:46:46,580 --> 00:46:48,880
He looks a lot like
I imagined he would.

745
00:46:49,680 --> 00:46:50,680
It's incredible, isn't it?

746
00:46:51,250 --> 00:46:52,880
He looks just like Grandfather did.

747
00:46:53,950 --> 00:46:58,350
So, you're going to Seongdam
this early just to post these?

748
00:46:58,650 --> 00:47:00,860
The clinic's closed
for the weekend anyway.

749
00:47:01,120 --> 00:47:02,560
I was just going to go
put some up and come back.

750
00:47:02,790 --> 00:47:05,590
Gosh, I don't know
if this is the right thing to do.

751
00:47:06,330 --> 00:47:09,570
You should be using this time
to look after Seong Mi.

752
00:47:10,230 --> 00:47:11,330
I'll be back before you know it.

753
00:47:11,770 --> 00:47:13,900
We all have to get together
to watch the premiere today.

754
00:47:14,140 --> 00:47:16,570
I'll give Seong Mi a foot rub
when I get back.

755
00:47:18,440 --> 00:47:21,480
All right.
Just don't be out too late.

756
00:47:22,110 --> 00:47:23,550
Okay. Let's go.

757
00:47:24,250 --> 00:47:25,780
- We'll be back.
- Okay.

758
00:47:36,830 --> 00:47:37,990
Unbelievable.

759
00:47:39,030 --> 00:47:43,330
- What now?
- Tell Dr. Han before she's here.

760
00:47:43,670 --> 00:47:46,640
I'm going to. That is the plan.

761
00:47:47,240 --> 00:47:48,800
You'd better handle this right,
Gong Ju Ah.

762
00:47:49,500 --> 00:47:51,270
I'm completely innocent in all this.

763
00:47:51,470 --> 00:47:54,710
The reason for this breakup
has to be all on you. Got it?

764
00:47:54,910 --> 00:47:57,810
Gosh, I get it! How many times
do you have to say it?

765
00:47:58,450 --> 00:48:01,750
I've already laid the groundwork
so no one gets mad. Don't worry.

766
00:48:10,890 --> 00:48:14,300
Okay, there. Here you go.

767
00:48:18,570 --> 00:48:19,570
How's the water?

768
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:21,400
It's good.

769
00:48:21,700 --> 00:48:24,710
I hear these alkaline water ionizers
are really popular these days.

770
00:48:24,840 --> 00:48:27,140
That's why I decided
to splurge on one.

771
00:48:28,010 --> 00:48:31,150
What's this for? Since when do you
spend so much on Parents' Day?

772
00:48:31,710 --> 00:48:33,720
You're not in some kind
of trouble, are you?

773
00:48:34,580 --> 00:48:35,580
Of course not.

774
00:48:36,020 --> 00:48:38,150
I don't know.
You look pretty guilty.

775
00:48:38,250 --> 00:48:41,190
Hey, you know how much I care
about this family.

776
00:48:41,590 --> 00:48:45,390
Anyway, hydration is important,
so make sure you all drink up. Okay?

777
00:48:46,030 --> 00:48:48,760
Okay, thank you.
I'll be sure to drink it.

778
00:48:49,100 --> 00:48:50,530
I'm going to go get ready.

779
00:49:02,240 --> 00:49:03,780
Did you break up with Jun Hyeok?

780
00:49:05,380 --> 00:49:10,050
- Gosh, your intuition is amazing.
- You should reconsider.

781
00:49:10,190 --> 00:49:12,220
I've thought this through,
and it's over.

782
00:49:12,520 --> 00:49:15,490
And don't go blaming Jun Hyeok.
It was all my fault.

783
00:49:16,530 --> 00:49:17,730
I'm sure it was.

784
00:49:20,530 --> 00:49:23,000
I can't come with you after work.
I'm busy.

785
00:49:24,430 --> 00:49:25,470
Don't worry about me.

786
00:49:25,730 --> 00:49:27,200
I have to go to the clinic
to pack up my things.

787
00:49:27,740 --> 00:49:28,770
Why are you packing up?

788
00:49:30,410 --> 00:49:33,340
I'm leaving the clinic to my junior
and taking a few months off.

789
00:49:34,040 --> 00:49:35,040
What?

790
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:36,980
Why, all of a sudden?

791
00:49:38,380 --> 00:49:40,150
What do you mean, "why?"
Because I want to.

792
00:49:40,980 --> 00:49:42,380
Because I'm exhausted.
Is that a problem?

793
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:46,190
How can you be so impulsive?
What about the show?

794
00:49:46,790 --> 00:49:48,590
I'm taking a break from the show
for a while, too.

795
00:49:48,860 --> 00:49:52,260
What is going on?
Did you at least tell the network?

796
00:49:52,860 --> 00:49:55,360
We chose you as our model because
everyone knows you from your show.

797
00:49:55,360 --> 00:49:56,970
What am I supposed to do now?

798
00:49:57,600 --> 00:50:01,240
I got Director Yang's approval,
so you just worry about yourself.

799
00:50:03,710 --> 00:50:06,740
Wait, why didn't Director Yang
say anything to me?

800
00:50:06,880 --> 00:50:09,010
Are you his boss?
Is he supposed to report to you?

801
00:50:09,780 --> 00:50:11,850
I guess you have a point.

802
00:50:12,450 --> 00:50:13,450
Unbelievable.

803
00:50:16,280 --> 00:50:18,820
I really tried to make things work,
ma'am.

804
00:50:18,890 --> 00:50:22,690
But it turns out, being friends
is completely different from dating.

805
00:50:23,930 --> 00:50:25,290
- Jun Hyeok, seriously...
- It was just too much for me.

806
00:50:25,360 --> 00:50:26,600
Could he be any more dramatic?

807
00:50:27,230 --> 00:50:30,070
I feel bad.
I hope this won't bother Dr. Han.

808
00:50:30,600 --> 00:50:34,100
It's fine.
She took it better than I expected.

809
00:50:36,100 --> 00:50:39,010
So, is she heading to the clinic
after her walking practice?

810
00:50:39,410 --> 00:50:42,110
She said she's going to the clinic
to pack up today.

811
00:50:42,910 --> 00:50:46,750
Hey, why didn't you tell me
she was taking a break from work?

812
00:50:47,450 --> 00:50:50,690
I thought it would be better
coming from her directly.

813
00:50:51,190 --> 00:50:53,690
Wouldn't it be strange for you
to find out from me?

814
00:51:01,930 --> 00:51:04,800
- Okay, time for our walk-through.
- Models, let's gather up.

815
00:51:17,110 --> 00:51:19,110
(Han Seong Mi
Neuropsychiatric Clinic)

816
00:51:21,180 --> 00:51:22,220
My gosh.

817
00:51:22,420 --> 00:51:23,920
It's the weekend.
Why are you all here?

818
00:51:24,450 --> 00:51:26,560
We had a feeling
you might come in today,

819
00:51:26,890 --> 00:51:28,320
so we came in to see you.

820
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:31,230
I came in on a day off specifically
to avoid saying goodbye.

821
00:51:31,660 --> 00:51:33,500
- Go on home now.
- No, it's fine.

822
00:51:33,830 --> 00:51:36,670
Since we're already here,
let us help you pack up.

823
00:51:36,830 --> 00:51:39,200
It's all right.
There's not much to pack.

824
00:51:39,970 --> 00:51:43,740
Right, did you give my patient files
to Dr. Kang?

825
00:51:44,140 --> 00:51:48,010
Yes. And we'll be sure to explain
the situation to the patients.

826
00:51:48,580 --> 00:51:52,580
I've already called my regulars
who rely heavily on our sessions.

827
00:51:53,320 --> 00:51:54,320
Okay.

828
00:51:55,420 --> 00:51:56,550
Oh, dear.

829
00:51:56,950 --> 00:52:00,920
- Cheer up. It's not like I'm dying.
- Doctor...

830
00:52:01,590 --> 00:52:05,860
- It's nothing too serious, is it?
- Of course not.

831
00:52:06,760 --> 00:52:09,400
I'm going to come back
in perfect health.

832
00:52:09,800 --> 00:52:13,070
I'll get my treatment,
come back safe and sound,

833
00:52:13,340 --> 00:52:15,000
and then on top of being
the Love Evangelist,

834
00:52:15,270 --> 00:52:16,940
I'll become the Hope Evangelist too,
why not?

835
00:52:18,310 --> 00:52:20,210
Stop making such a fuss and go home.

836
00:52:20,880 --> 00:52:22,540
I'll see you all in a few months,
okay?

837
00:52:22,980 --> 00:52:24,310
You've got this, Doctor!

838
00:52:24,850 --> 00:52:25,880
Stay strong!

839
00:52:28,850 --> 00:52:30,120
Thanks.

840
00:52:31,320 --> 00:52:34,420
- Now, hurry up and go home.
- Okay, we're going. Bye.

841
00:52:34,490 --> 00:52:35,560
Thanks for everything.

842
00:52:37,590 --> 00:52:39,490
(Han Seong Mi, Psychiatrist)

843
00:52:47,300 --> 00:52:48,640
(Han Seong Mi, Psychiatrist)

844
00:53:00,250 --> 00:53:02,780
(Morning: Outpatient Appointments)

845
00:53:02,920 --> 00:53:04,750
(Mental Health Case Review,
Stress-Induced Emotion Suppression)

846
00:53:04,820 --> 00:53:06,590
(Morning: New Patient Consultations)

847
00:53:06,690 --> 00:53:07,920
Han Seong Mi.

848
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:10,460
You've really worked hard
your whole life.

849
00:53:26,210 --> 00:53:27,910
(Consultation Room)

850
00:53:27,980 --> 00:53:29,740
(Han Seong Mi, Psychiatrist,
Clinic Director)

851
00:53:34,750 --> 00:53:37,420
My gosh.
Director Yang, what brings you here?

852
00:53:37,850 --> 00:53:39,790
What do you think?
I heard you were packing up.

853
00:53:40,220 --> 00:53:42,760
Goodness, you shouldn't be lifting
something this heavy alone.

854
00:53:42,820 --> 00:53:45,260
It's fine. It's just small things.
It's not heavy. Give it to me.

855
00:53:45,260 --> 00:53:47,600
Please, you can't push yourself.

856
00:53:47,830 --> 00:53:50,830
Give me your keys.
I'll drive you home.

857
00:53:50,900 --> 00:53:53,370
No, that's okay.
I can manage on my own.

858
00:53:53,440 --> 00:53:56,000
I have to head to my parents' place
to watch the show anyway.

859
00:53:56,070 --> 00:53:58,840
Then just take your own car.
I'll take mine.

860
00:53:58,970 --> 00:54:02,340
If you keep this up,
I'll tell Gong Ju Ah everything.

861
00:54:07,150 --> 00:54:08,220
(3H Acupressure Bed)

862
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:09,380
So this is your new store, Se Ri.

863
00:54:09,880 --> 00:54:12,220
(3H Acupressure Bed)

864
00:54:12,290 --> 00:54:13,290
Hello.

865
00:54:14,060 --> 00:54:17,760
So, you'll be the new owner here
starting next week, right?

866
00:54:17,830 --> 00:54:18,830
Yes.

867
00:54:19,530 --> 00:54:21,200
I'm sorry to keep bothering you.

868
00:54:21,260 --> 00:54:24,030
Not at all. It's better for you
to come often and learn the ropes.

869
00:54:25,330 --> 00:54:29,140
Weren't you going to Seongdam today?
Why did you tag along?

870
00:54:29,540 --> 00:54:32,510
It was just to hang some flyers.
They asked me to help out.

871
00:54:32,940 --> 00:54:35,680
I felt bad for letting you
prepare the store all by yourself.

872
00:54:36,240 --> 00:54:39,380
Come on.
You've been busy with filming.

873
00:54:39,580 --> 00:54:42,820
Just be patient with me.
I'll help more when I'm less busy.

874
00:54:44,550 --> 00:54:46,150
- Look over there.
- Should I?

875
00:54:46,590 --> 00:54:47,690
Delivery.

876
00:54:48,390 --> 00:54:49,920
- Over here.
- Okay.

877
00:54:50,860 --> 00:54:51,860
Is it nice?

878
00:54:58,430 --> 00:55:00,140
My gosh, hello.

879
00:55:00,200 --> 00:55:02,070
(Shinna Snack Bar)

880
00:55:02,140 --> 00:55:04,940
- You're the doctor.
- So? Did you see an orthopedist?

881
00:55:05,640 --> 00:55:09,080
- Right. I'll be sure to go.
- Come on, now.

882
00:55:09,310 --> 00:55:12,250
It'll get serious
if you leave it untreated.

883
00:55:12,250 --> 00:55:13,380
Okay.

884
00:55:13,750 --> 00:55:15,880
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thanks.

885
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:23,830
This is nice. Very nice.

886
00:55:27,660 --> 00:55:30,300
If you see anyone
who looks like him,

887
00:55:30,300 --> 00:55:32,430
please give us a call. Thank you.

888
00:55:32,570 --> 00:55:35,800
If you see anyone
who looks like him, call us.

889
00:55:39,310 --> 00:55:41,240
He shouldn't have taken it
just to throw it out.

890
00:55:43,680 --> 00:55:44,680
Darn it.

891
00:55:46,010 --> 00:55:47,250
It happens.

892
00:55:48,550 --> 00:55:49,580
- Hey.
- Yes?

893
00:55:49,580 --> 00:55:51,120
Let's just hand them out
inside the shops.

894
00:55:51,520 --> 00:55:54,590
The shops? Let's just post these up
in a few more spots here, okay?

895
00:55:54,660 --> 00:55:55,720
Come on.

896
00:55:56,020 --> 00:55:59,990
Excuse me, ma'am? Would it be okay
to put this up out front?

897
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:03,230
- Sure, go ahead.
- Thank you.

898
00:56:03,430 --> 00:56:05,370
(Missing Person, Gong Gi Cheol)

899
00:56:05,730 --> 00:56:07,100
(Gong Gi Cheol,
went missing at age 42)

900
00:56:07,170 --> 00:56:08,270
(Gu In Ok, went missing at age 43)

901
00:56:08,640 --> 00:56:11,640
Hello. If you see anyone
who looks similar,

902
00:56:11,840 --> 00:56:13,840
please give us a call.

903
00:56:14,680 --> 00:56:16,640
I think we've covered
this whole area.

904
00:56:17,210 --> 00:56:19,280
If we still don't get a call
after all this,

905
00:56:19,980 --> 00:56:21,420
we should just file a police report.

906
00:56:21,950 --> 00:56:23,720
Let's just wait a little bit longer,
okay?

907
00:56:24,020 --> 00:56:26,150
I'm almost out. We have a few left.

908
00:56:26,150 --> 00:56:28,420
- I still have a bunch left.
- Let's put them up. Come on.

909
00:56:28,490 --> 00:56:30,260
No, I'm serious. I have a lot left.

910
00:56:30,360 --> 00:56:32,060
(Missing Person)

911
00:56:32,130 --> 00:56:35,530
- All done?
- Yes. We've posted all of them.

912
00:56:36,130 --> 00:56:37,130
My gosh.

913
00:56:40,240 --> 00:56:42,240
Isn't that the old man
from the tailor shop?

914
00:56:43,200 --> 00:56:44,210
Excuse me?

915
00:56:44,810 --> 00:56:46,370
I'm pretty sure it's him.

916
00:56:46,810 --> 00:56:49,980
The man who only does tailoring
in the back.

917
00:56:51,050 --> 00:56:55,880
- Where is that?
- Yes. The tailor shop, over there.

918
00:56:56,380 --> 00:56:57,520
Over there?

919
00:56:57,950 --> 00:57:00,190
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

920
00:57:00,260 --> 00:57:01,260
Thank you.

921
00:57:01,590 --> 00:57:03,190
- Dae Han.
- Let's go!

922
00:57:03,260 --> 00:57:04,330
- Hurry up.
- Come on, let's go!

923
00:57:04,390 --> 00:57:07,130
- Is this the place?
- Hey, here! It's right here!

924
00:57:07,200 --> 00:57:08,200
The tailor shop.

925
00:57:08,500 --> 00:57:10,170
- Here it is.
- The tailor shop, this is it.

926
00:57:10,230 --> 00:57:11,670
Wait a second.

927
00:57:12,430 --> 00:57:13,430
Hey.

928
00:57:14,100 --> 00:57:16,470
It might not be him.
Don't get your hopes up, okay?

929
00:57:17,970 --> 00:57:21,780
I just have a gut feeling it's him.
Just a second.

930
00:57:21,840 --> 00:57:23,010
(Alterations)

931
00:57:25,410 --> 00:57:26,410
Are you good?

932
00:57:26,750 --> 00:57:28,320
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

933
00:57:29,220 --> 00:57:30,320
Yes.

934
00:57:33,120 --> 00:57:35,060
Now, you're making me nervous.
Darn it.

935
00:57:43,000 --> 00:57:45,900
What? Are they closed today?

936
00:57:48,170 --> 00:57:49,300
What's this?

937
00:57:49,740 --> 00:57:53,110
They packed up and moved out
the other day.

938
00:57:53,610 --> 00:57:55,610
- What?
- Where to?

939
00:57:56,310 --> 00:57:57,310
I have no idea.

940
00:58:00,250 --> 00:58:01,650
We should've come sooner.

941
00:58:02,420 --> 00:58:03,420
Seriously.

942
00:58:05,190 --> 00:58:06,220
Darn it.

943
00:58:10,460 --> 00:58:11,460
Excuse me.

944
00:58:11,530 --> 00:58:12,930
(Shinna Snack Bar)

945
00:58:15,230 --> 00:58:16,230
Can we...

946
00:58:16,870 --> 00:58:18,400
go talk somewhere for a minute?

947
00:58:29,780 --> 00:58:31,280
You want me to act like
I don't know you?

948
00:58:32,250 --> 00:58:33,310
Please.

949
00:58:34,020 --> 00:58:35,750
I've moved on,
and I'm doing just fine.

950
00:58:40,290 --> 00:58:41,290
Fine.

951
00:58:42,660 --> 00:58:43,690
Thank you.

952
00:58:44,130 --> 00:58:45,590
But let me ask you one thing.

953
00:58:46,560 --> 00:58:49,860
Back when Jong Gil died,
you were pregnant, right?

954
00:58:50,530 --> 00:58:52,030
That kid I saw you with
the other day...

955
00:58:52,870 --> 00:58:53,940
Is she your daughter?

956
00:59:01,810 --> 00:59:04,410
No. I didn't have the baby.

957
00:59:05,480 --> 00:59:06,610
That baby...

958
00:59:07,780 --> 00:59:08,780
I got rid of it.

959
00:59:30,170 --> 00:59:31,410
What are you looking for?

960
00:59:34,540 --> 00:59:35,640
Eun Bin.

961
00:59:36,510 --> 00:59:40,150
Are you looking for that box
that was wrapped in a cloth?

962
00:59:41,580 --> 00:59:42,620
Yes.

963
00:59:43,020 --> 00:59:46,020
I threw it out.
It didn't seem important.

964
00:59:48,390 --> 00:59:49,960
Did you open it?

965
00:59:50,290 --> 00:59:52,090
No. You said it was just soap,
right?

966
00:59:52,360 --> 00:59:54,500
Yes, that's right. It's just soap.

967
00:59:58,030 --> 01:00:00,270
What are you doing?
Let's get ready to watch the show.

968
01:00:12,080 --> 01:00:16,120
And I have my husband to thank
for keeping my skin this radiant.

969
01:00:16,250 --> 01:00:18,650
For three years in a row at the
Korean Medicine Doctors' Conference!

970
01:00:18,720 --> 01:00:20,250
For three years in a row!

971
01:00:20,390 --> 01:00:22,690
He earned
the title of "Golden Hands."

972
01:00:23,320 --> 01:00:25,430
You could call it
his "acupuncture of love."

973
01:00:25,430 --> 01:00:26,460
Nice!

974
01:00:27,900 --> 01:00:30,970
Wow, the camera really loves you.

975
01:00:31,600 --> 01:00:32,930
Stop.

976
01:00:33,800 --> 01:00:35,500
Auntie, are you crying?

977
01:00:36,770 --> 01:00:41,010
I'm just so happy, I'm tearing up.

978
01:00:41,080 --> 01:00:44,910
- You're being so sentimental.
- I know, right?

979
01:00:45,850 --> 01:00:48,150
It's just...
Being on the show together...

980
01:00:48,680 --> 01:00:51,390
makes me feel finally accepted
as part of the family.

981
01:00:51,650 --> 01:00:54,960
Hey, what are you talking about?
Of course, you're family.

982
01:00:55,990 --> 01:00:57,390
You've worked so hard, honey.

983
01:01:10,410 --> 01:01:13,840
- These seasoned veggies are good.
- Yes.

984
01:01:14,180 --> 01:01:17,480
These greens are good for immunity,
so eat up, everyone.

985
01:01:17,550 --> 01:01:18,550
- Okay.
- Yes.

986
01:01:18,610 --> 01:01:21,250
And especially you, Woo Jae.
You need to take care of yourself.

987
01:01:21,320 --> 01:01:22,320
Eat up.

988
01:01:22,420 --> 01:01:24,090
Hey, you really need to eat more.
Here, try this.

989
01:01:24,150 --> 01:01:27,020
Would Grandpa be watching this
from somewhere?

990
01:01:27,460 --> 01:01:30,490
- Who knows?
- Man, this is delicious.

991
01:01:30,730 --> 01:01:31,730
Mother.

992
01:01:32,560 --> 01:01:36,500
You've worked so hard
to take care of our family.

993
01:01:37,500 --> 01:01:40,800
What are you talking about?
It wasn't just me. Goodness.

994
01:01:46,070 --> 01:01:49,480
- The rice is perfect.
- Dad, try some of this.

995
01:01:49,540 --> 01:01:51,510
You shouldn't have.

996
01:01:51,880 --> 01:01:53,650
It's some fresh cabbage kimchi.

997
01:01:53,980 --> 01:01:56,820
It's nice and crunchy. It's so good!

998
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:59,790
Goodness, but you already brought me
the braised beans...

999
01:01:59,850 --> 01:02:02,390
and a ton of stir-fried anchovies.

1000
01:02:02,860 --> 01:02:06,990
- Hello, ma'am!
- Yes. Right.

1001
01:02:07,260 --> 01:02:09,960
Yes, you shouldn't bend your knees
too much.

1002
01:02:10,030 --> 01:02:11,900
Yes, keep them straight like this
whenever possible.

1003
01:02:12,000 --> 01:02:15,300
Okay, let's focus on the infrared
and manual therapy...

1004
01:02:15,300 --> 01:02:16,400
I'm here.

1005
01:02:16,470 --> 01:02:18,840
Does it hurt a lot when I do this?
I'm going to lift it one more time.

1006
01:02:18,910 --> 01:02:19,910
How about when I lift it like this?

1007
01:02:19,970 --> 01:02:21,280
At this point,
I think she needs manual therapy.

1008
01:02:21,340 --> 01:02:22,880
All right,
go ahead and lower it. Yes.

1009
01:02:23,540 --> 01:02:26,350
Try to lift it up one more time.
No, slowly.

1010
01:02:26,410 --> 01:02:28,120
Just use your own strength. Yes.

1011
01:02:30,220 --> 01:02:31,920
Leave it. I want to watch this.

1012
01:02:31,990 --> 01:02:35,260
Do you really think this is the time
to be lazing around watching TV?

1013
01:02:35,490 --> 01:02:37,460
Come on, turn it on. Let me watch.

1014
01:02:37,730 --> 01:02:41,200
Get to work!
The cost of moving because of you...

1015
01:02:41,330 --> 01:02:42,600
That's not just a few bucks,
you know.

1016
01:02:42,800 --> 01:02:45,430
Look, I get it, okay?
Now, turn it on.

1017
01:02:45,500 --> 01:02:47,240
My goodness.
Seriously, what is with you?

1018
01:02:47,300 --> 01:02:51,570
Because this place looks familiar.
And the people look familiar too.

1019
01:02:51,710 --> 01:02:53,040
There's no way.

1020
01:02:53,170 --> 01:02:57,680
Let go.
I'm about to remember something.

1021
01:03:30,750 --> 01:03:33,180
(Recipe For Love)

1022
01:03:33,250 --> 01:03:37,080
Stop dragging your feet and remarry.
If you still want a kid so badly,

1023
01:03:37,150 --> 01:03:41,190
- you need to hurry up, man.
- I don't want to have kids.

1024
01:03:44,490 --> 01:03:47,430
Now that more people recognize us,
it could become a hassle.

1025
01:03:47,500 --> 01:03:48,730
Okay, one...

1026
01:03:49,960 --> 01:03:51,630
When I have some time,
I'll go back and...

1027
01:03:51,770 --> 01:03:55,040
- check CCTV near the tailor shop...
- Tailor shop?

1028
01:03:55,900 --> 01:03:59,070
What do you think about having Se Ri
adopt Hyun Bin and Eun Bin?

1029
01:03:59,210 --> 01:04:02,940
- Adoption?
- We'd get Mom's fortune, right?

1030
01:04:03,280 --> 01:04:06,550
So if you find out where she lives,
what are you planning to do?

1031
01:04:06,610 --> 01:04:10,380
Should I be a villain, end her joy,
and take everything she has?
